7. Voluntary Contact
If you would like to keep up to date with the latest happenings at Infiniteach, feel free to voluntarily sign up for our e-newsletters. You can opt out of these newsletters, and any other contact with us, at any time. Simply email us at:
info@infiniteach.com
.
If you contact us for any reason, we will use your information to respond to you regarding the reason you contacted us. We will NOT sell or share your information with any third party outside of our organization, other than as needed to fulfill your request, i.e. to ship an order, or as otherwise set forth in this Privacy Policy.
8. Keeping your personal information secure
Infiniteach takes the trust you place in us seriously. To prevent unauthorized access or disclosure, to maintain data accuracy, and to ensure the appropriate use of the information, Infiniteach utilizes generally accepted industry standards to protect your Personal Identifiable Information submitted to us. No method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure, therefore we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your Personal Identifiable Information.
9. Website Tracking
On our website, we may use cookies, web beacons, or related files only to track your site usage. We do NOT collect personal information through cookies and will not sell or rent this information with third parties. We mostly want to see where you’re getting stuck so that we can fix it! Cookies can be disabled through your browser’s settings. Keep in mind that disabling cookies may result in some features of the Service not working properly.
Cookies help us to understand your website usage, so we can continually improve its usability. For example, we may use cookies to personalize your experience on our website, if you have accepted this option (e.g., to remember your customer ID on a login page). During the period you are logged into our site, we log IP addresses (a number assigned to your computer when you use the Internet), browser and platform types, domain name, access times, referral data (the last site or URL you visited before logging into our site and the first site or URL you visit after leaving our site), and your activity while using our site.
There are two types of cookies you may encounter when using our Services. First Party Cookies are our own cookies controlled by us and used to provide information about usage of our site. Third party cookies are set by third party sites. We do not have control over third party cookies. One of the third party cookies we use is the web analysis tool, “Google Analytics”. Google Analytics is a popular web analytics service provided by Google to help us analyze how users use our Services. Find out more about how these cookies are used on Google’s privacy site.
10. Security
Please remember that any information transferred over the Internet could potentially be accessed by unauthorized parties, and therefore, we cannot guarantee the security of data transmitted via our Services. We do make every effort to secure any personal information you provide, and will only require the minimal amount of information we need to provide our Services or process your request.
11. Changes to this statement
The terms of the Privacy Policy may change from time to time without notice to you unless required by law. If we modify our Privacy Policy, we will post the revised statement here, with an updated revision date. To make sure that you are aware of the most recent Privacy Policy, you should review this page periodically.
12. Questions? Concerns? Feedback?
